    • Class edu.cpp.cs.cs141.class_project.GameEngine extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • gamer

          VisualGame gamer
          An object that encapsulates the multiple parts of the GUI. By placing those parts in one class, it is easier to avoid stackoverflow errors due to indirect recursion

        • message

          GUIMessage message
          The class responsible creating pop up messages. These messages contain warnings for when the player tries to make an illegal move. They also contain bits of information for when the player picks up power-ups

        • grid

          Grid grid
          This is the 2 dimensional array that the player is traversing through The array keeps track of the location of all objects within the array.

        • userI

          UserInterface userI
          This class allows the user to interact with the game. The userInterface is also responsible for any output text that is printer on to the console.

        • hasMoved

          boolean hasMoved
          determines whether or not the player has moved A player cannot move when this is false

        • direction

          int direction
          Determines what direction the player is facing 1) up 2) down 3) left 4) right The player can only see in the direction they are facing

        • hasLooked

          boolean hasLooked
          Determines whether or not the player has looked already or not The player cannot look again until this variable is false;

        • gun

          Gun gun
          The gun that the player is holding. This gun starts off with one ammo and loses one ammo every time it is fired. The gun can be reloaded if the player finds a bullet The gun cannot shoot when it has no ammo.

        • invincible

          int invincible
          The number of turns that the player is invincible. While this number is greater than zero, the player cannot die.

        • win

          boolean win
          A variable for keeping track of whether or not the player has won. The player cannot perform any actions if they win.

        • alive

          boolean alive
          A variable for keeping track of whether or not the player is alive. The player cannot perform any actions if they are not alive.

        • hardMode

          boolean hardMode
          A variable for keeping track of the difficulty of the game. If hardMode is true, the enemy gain an AI and will chase the player when they are in the same row or column

        • debug

          boolean debug
          A variable for keeping track of whether or not the game is being debugged or played If this is true, the game enters a debugging mode, where all the objects within the grid can be seen. The exit is also visible.

        • hasRadar

          boolean hasRadar
          Determines if the player has a radar If the player has a radar, they know the location of the exit.

        • gui

          boolean gui
          Determines if the gui is running or not. If the gui is running, pop-up messages will appear instead of text on the console A graohical representation of the grid will also be shown instead of a text based one

    • Class edu.cpp.cs.cs141.class_project.GamePlayer extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • game

          Data game
          The object that is responsible for saving and loading. This also the GamePlayer to also be able to use save and load

        • frame

          javax.swing.JFrame frame
          A window that contains all the components of the GUI

        • panel

          javax.swing.JPanel panel
          A panel that is used for organizing the 2d array. The layout that will be used with this panel is gridbaglayout

        • gbc

          java.awt.GridBagConstraints gbc
          An object that control the spacing of the components within the panel This control the spacing of the JLabels with the images

        • textGBC

          java.awt.GridBagConstraints textGBC
          An object that control the spacing of the components within the panel This controls the spacing of the JLabels with text.

        • menuBar

          javax.swing.JMenuBar menuBar
          The menu that contains many options for player to perform numerous tasks The 3 options are: File, Options, and Mode

        • mntmExit

          javax.swing.JMenuItem mntmExit
          An exit option that exists in the menu under File This option will cause the whole entire JFrame to close.

        • mntmSave

          javax.swing.JMenuItem mntmSave
          A save option that exists in the menu under File This option allows the player to save the gameEngine and give a custom name to their save file

        • mntmLoad

          javax.swing.JMenuItem mntmLoad
          A load option that exists in the menu under File This option allows the player to load a gameEngine by specifying which file to load.

        • mnFile

          javax.swing.JMenu mnFile
          A File category that exists within the menu. The file category contains options for saving, loading, and exiting.

        • mnOptions

          javax.swing.JMenu mnOptions
          An options category that exists within the menu. The option category contains the two difficulties: Easy mode and Hard Mode

        • rdbtnmntmEasyMode

          javax.swing.JRadioButtonMenuItem rdbtnmntmEasyMode
          A option to change the game's mode to easy mode. In easy mode the enemy's movements are completely random. Since this is a radio button, this cannot be selected at the same time as hard mode

        • rdbtnmntmHardMode

          javax.swing.JRadioButtonMenuItem rdbtnmntmHardMode
          An option to change the game's mode to hard mode. In hard mode, the enemy has advanced AI and are capable of following the player Since this is a radio button, this cannot be selected at the same time as easy mode.

        • group

          javax.swing.ButtonGroup group
          The group that contains the two radio buttons for easy mode and hard mode This makes it so that only one of the two buttons can be pressed at a time.

        • debugGroup

          javax.swing.ButtonGroup debugGroup
          The group that contains the two radio buttons for normal mode and debug mode This makes is so that only one of the two buttons can be presssed at a time.

        • direction

          int direction
          This is the direction that the player is facing. 1) up 2) down 3) left 4) right

        • mnMode

          javax.swing.JMenu mnMode
          A category that exists within the menu. This category contains the options: Normal Mode and Debug Mode

        • rdbtnmntmNormalMode

          javax.swing.JRadioButtonMenuItem rdbtnmntmNormalMode
          An option to change the game to normal mode In normal mode, the player can only see two space in the direction that they are looking. Since this is a radio button, this cannot be selected at the same time as debug mode

        • rdbtnmntmDebugMode

          javax.swing.JRadioButtonMenuItem rdbtnmntmDebugMode
          An option to change the game to debug mode In debug mode, the player can see all of the objects within the grid. Since this is a radio button, this cannot be selected at the same time as normal mode
